title.narrative: IMMUNIZATION PLUS

description.narrative: Women and children have equitable access to preventive and promotional interventions for the adoption of healthy behaviour in matters of health and STI-HIV/AIDS including humanitarian situation, which contributes to Adolescent Health And Nutrition, Child Health, Immunization. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Operational Support To Programme Delivery, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: Mothers, newborns and particularly the most disadvantaged have equitable access to high-impact quality interventions to ensure their survival and development, including in humanitarian situations

description.narrative: UNICEF continued to advocate and to support the Government for the acquisition of traditional vaccines. All the vaccines that had been planned were acquired despite delays in disbursement which caused some vaccine shortages. Support for priority issues concerning inventory management and equipment maintenance continued, with a field mission to put equipment back into service, assess maintenance practices, train sub-national inventory managers, and provide support for the implementation of input management plans for COVID-19 vaccination campaigns. A full Effective Vaccine Management (EVM) assessment is planned for January 2022. | Status:Met | As-of Date:08/01/2022
